rComments: These are misleading reviews! Worst class ever taken. Used to enjoy french but she really made me question majoring in it. Everyone I talked to that's had her as a prof, even for the oral course says she lectures the whole time and takes marks off for silly reasons. You might be okay if you participate a lot and fight for yourself and your marks!GL

I had this prof for FRE180, FRE181, FRE280, also FRE241. She was awesome! Her lectures and instructions were quite clear. Make sure to study the textbooks, do your readings, and do the exercises. They will help you with answering questions for participation marks and they will prepare you well for quizzes, tests and the exam.

She's a sweet, caring prof but her lectures are so boring. Maybe I felt this way because it was a full year course and was sick of it by the end. She tries to make class fun but usually, the activities she comes up with end up being worse than lectures.

rComments: She was a really good prof. Every instructions were clear.

She cares about you as an individual and helps you understand, but when it comes to her tests (ESPECIALLY THE FRENCH LISTENING TEST), shes a hard marker. Overall, shes caring and genuinely wants you to succeed.  ALSO NO TEXTBOOK NEEDED FOR THIS COURSE!!!!!

Caroline Lebrec is so kind and really cares about her students succeeding. She is very approachable and gives good feedback in class and in office hours. She is from Lyon, France, and it was great to have a native France French speaker teaching the class on written and oral French. I would definitely take her again!
